Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Stranton in Hartlepool 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1936 and added to the parish of Hartlepool.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Seaton Carew. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1921 and added to the parish of West Hartlepool. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of West Hartlepool 
    and Dalton Piercy. See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Hart, Monk 
    Hesleden and Hartlepool. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (b).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and added to the parish of Hartlepool. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Throston. Abolished 
    1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of West Hartlepool and Elwick.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Stranton in West Hartlepool 
    Municipal Borough. See also Table 2, note (d).
